{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd2e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2685"},"text":"§ 2685.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Adjustment of or surcharge on selling prices in commissary stores to provide funds for construction and improvement of commissary store facilities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd2f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Adjustment or Surcharge Authorized","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Secretary of Defense may, for the purposes of this section, provide for an adjustment of, or surcharge on, sales prices of goods and services sold in commissary store facilities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd30-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Use for Construction, Repair, Improvement, and Maintenance","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd31-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense may use the proceeds from the adjustments or surcharges authorized by subsection (a) only—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd32-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to acquire (including acquisition by lease), construct, convert, expand, improve, repair, maintain, and equip the physical infrastructure of commissary stores and central product processing facilities of the defense commissary system; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd33-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to cover environmental evaluation and construction costs related to activities described in paragraph (1), including costs for surveys, administration, overhead, planning, and design.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd34-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In paragraph (1), the term “physical infrastructure” includes real property, utilities, and equipment (installed and free standing and including computer equipment), necessary to provide a complete and usable commissary store or central product processing facility.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd35-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Advance Obligation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Defense, with the approval of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, may obligate anticipated proceeds from the adjustments or surcharges authorized by subsection (a) for any use specified in subsection (b) or (d), without regard to fiscal year limitations, if the Secretary determines that such obligation is necessary to carry out any use of such adjustments or surcharges specified in subsection (b) or (d).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd36-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Cooperation With Nonappropriated Fund Instrumentalities","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd37-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Defense may authorize a nonappropriated fund instrumentality of the United States to enter into a contract for construction of a shopping mall or similar facility for a commissary store and one or more nonappropriated fund instrumentality activities. The Secretary may use the proceeds of adjustments or surcharges authorized by subsection (a) to reimburse the nonappropriated fund instrumentality for the portion of the cost of the contract that is attributable to construction of the commissary store or to pay the contractor directly for that portion of such cost.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd38-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In paragraph (1), the term “construction”, with respect to a facility, includes acquisition, conversion, expansion, installation, or other improvement of the facility.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd39-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Other Sources of Funds for Construction and Improvements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Revenues received by the Secretary of Defense from the following sources or activities of commissary store facilities shall be available for the purposes set forth in subsections (b), (c), and (d):","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Sale of recyclable materials.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Sale of excess and surplus property.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" License fees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Royalties.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2685/e/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Fees paid by sources of products in order to obtain favorable display of the products for resale, known as business related management fees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9aacd3f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/552/tVI/s611"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–552, title VI, § 611","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1765"},"text":"88 Stat. 1765","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/82/tVI/s614"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–82, title VI, § 614","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/380"},"text":"91 Stat. 380","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/321/tVIII/s804"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–321, title VIII, § 804","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1572"},"text":"96 Stat. 1572","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dB/tXXVIII/s2851"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. B, title XXVIII, § 2851","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3072"},"text":"108 Stat. 3072","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/dA/tIII/s374"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, div. A, title III, § 374","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/1707"},"text":"111 Stat. 1707","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(a), (b)], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–60.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9aacd40-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9aacd41-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida9aacd42-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(b)(1)], substituted “Secretary of Defense” for “Secretary of a military department, under regulations established by him and approved by the Secretary of Defense,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(a)], amended heading and text of subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Secretary of a military department, under regulations established by him and approved by the Secretary of Defense, may use the proceeds from the adjustments or surcharges authorized by subsection (a) to acquire, construct, convert, expand, install, or otherwise improve commissary store facilities at defense installations and for related environmental evaluation and construction costs, including surveys, administration, overhead, planning, and design.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(b)(2)], substituted “Secretary of Defense, with the approval of” for “Secretary of a military department, with the approval of the Secretary of Defense and” and “Secretary determines” for “Secretary of the military department determines”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(b)(3)], substituted “Secretary of Defense” for “Secretary of a military department”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsecs. (a) to (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s374/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 374(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted subsec. headings."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/85/s374/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–85, § 374(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s2851/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 2851(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or (d)” after “subsection (b)” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s2851/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, § 2851(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/321"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–321","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/82"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–82","children":[],"tail":" struck out “within the United States” after “defense installations”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida9aacd43-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida9aacd44-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2000 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–398, § 1 [[div. A]","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 333(c)], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1654"},"text":"114 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":", 1654A–60, provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/398/s1/dA"},"text":"“The amendment made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall take effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2001-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2001","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
